column3:
From Expanse. This was a favorite among the other guys on the Legacy team. Lots of walls to clamber around on, with a lot of freedom for planning unique routes.

It's a lot of fun to play, and therefore, in my professional opinion, you should play it.
From Expanse. I love this for its aesthetics and its uniqueness. There are a lot of gameplay elements here that I haven't seen used before. Have fun with it.

From Expanse. An awesome little map with some opportunities for experimenting with different routes. A lot of fun, and I think the difficulty is really well balanced. You can stay aboveground the whole time or dip into the floorguard tunnel below.
From Expanse. The map looks kind of Mount Doom II-esque, but plays a lot differently. The multiple exits allow for a lot of gameplay variety, and the launchpads help keep the flow going.

Recently I went back and played through my maps from Legacy's Expanse pack, and decided to post the five I consider my best to Numa. This one is pretty slow paced overall, with the notable exception of the bottom floorguard section. It doesn't require a lot of skill to beat, but it's quirky and subtle and I find the gameplay elements very interesting. I really like the aesthetics here as well; the map has kind of a subterranean vibe to it.

As usual, all gold is strongly encouraged. Enjoy.

Three days of playtesting, and I think I have me a solid map on my hands. very difficult, there's a definite trick to the switches up top, but you technically only need one to finish the level. I had a lot of fun playtesting this, and I feel it's good enough for NC6. So, it's submission time!

And I'll only provide a completion demo after someone else plays through it.
Presenting the world's first no-enemy survival map. That I know of at least. Have fun.

Ahh, the Simple Challenge series. It's been so long.

Extremely difficult, requires precise walljumping. Good luck.

From Vehemence 2.

Possibly my favorite of the pack. You can beat it in under five seconds like a true WarioWare style microgame, but playing around with different gold routes is a lot of fun as well.

From Vehemence 2.

I guess you could call this a spiritual sequel to my old Minimalist Series. All that gold, there for the taking, just out of your reach. And yes, all of it is possible to get. So get to it.

From Vehemence 2.

Yeah, it looks pretty run-of-the-mill, but it's actually a lot of fun. The lasers offer a decent amount of challenge without ever being overwhelming.

Go for the gold. All the cool kids are doing it.

From Vehemence 2.

Don't let the floorguards getcha.

Over the next few days I'll be submitting five of my favorite maps from my Vehemence 2 pack. If you'd like to get involved with Vehemence 2 or just want to play the maps, you can find the thread here: http://metanet.2.forumer.com/index.php?showtopic=18453&st=0

This map is fairly conventional in style, but what I like about it is the blend of high-flying and wallclinging elements. Go for gold, not just completion.

column3:
Ok, now before you get it into your head that this level is your enemy, let me tell you something - this map is your friend. I created it because when I saw anything with mines in a 2-block high tunnel (like in The Many and some other levels), I froze, lost a lot of valuable time, and promptly jumped into the mines, tearing myself to shreds.

So I made this map to practice and immunize myself against similar attacks in future. It worked for me - and it can work for you too :P

This is a map you can keep coming back to, it grows with you as your N prowess gets greater. See how many golden N's you can collect... I worked a lot on the difficulty curve, adding progressively more tricky techniques as you descend into the spiral. It actually turned out quite fun IMO, but I'm not expecting too high a vote, if any... Just remeber...   This map WILL make you a better player ;P
